title: EXPOSING THE INDIAN EDUCATION SYSTEM | Vaibhav Kadnar | Hindi
description:
In this video, Vaibhav Kadnar talks about how the Indian education system in current society is not providing the desired output to the nation as expected. Vaibhav dives deep into the education system currently present in India and discusses the various aspects which are restrictive in its nature and what needs to be done in order for India to emerge from it.

This video will help you understand the current education standards present in India and how even though people graduate from top tier colleges the country is not able to provide jobs to the students. 

In 2024, only 36% of 2000 students from IIT Bombay got a placement after their studies. This is alarming as to how even passing out from India’s best educational institute cannot guarantee you a job in India. So you can only imagine the state of students who pass out from tier 2,3 and 4 colleges in the nation. 

What are the reasons behind this? Who is responsible for the failure of the Indian education system? Do these students not have the relevant industry skills? Our education system of schools and colleges even after 15-20 years of academic years fails to make student employment worthy!

In this video, Vaibhav will also be covering the topics such as:

What is wrong with the Indian Education System?
How Indian education just focuses on marks and creates a pressure on the student.
How Indian schools neglect non-academic skills.
How it affects the mental health and self esteem of a student.

The Indian education system has curriculums and teaching methods  which are outdated.
How they teach kids in foreign countries like Finland and what India can learn from them.
Indian schools and colleges have teachers who are not qualified enough or literate enough to teach the students.

Rote learning and not any real understanding.
Practical learning is missing in our educational system.
Career paths beyond the normal rat race.
Job opportunities apart from being a doctor, engineer or civil services.
How entrepreneurs, business men and CEO's have the most money in the world.
Entrepreneurship is discouraged in India.

And finally what can be done to resolve all of this.
Educational reforms by the government of India
Technology in education to help learn

Please subscribe to the channel Vaibhav Kadnar for more such amazing informative content in the future.

Thank you!

title: Pro Kabaddi 2019 Highlights |Tamil Thalaivas vs Bengaluru Bulls | Hindi M45
description:
[Video Courtesy: Star Sports] Pawan Sehrawat and Nandal star as Bengaluru Bulls win on opening night in Chennai

‘Hi-Flyer’ Pawan Sehrawat scored his fifth Super 10 while Saurabh Nandal scored his second High 5 of the season in their team’s win.

A fifth Super 10 of the season from ‘Hi-Flyer’ Pawan Sehrawat and a second career High 5 from Saurabh Nandal helped Bengaluru Bullscurb their two-match losing streak and beat Tamil Thalaivas by a scoreline of 32-21 at the Jawaharlal Nehru Indoor Stadium in Chennai on Saturday.

Sehrawat was off to an unbelievable start as he scored a point in all but two of his first seven raid attempts. The Bengaluru Bulls defence, too, starved Tamil Thalaivas’ offence for points and tackled Ajay Thakur and Shabeer Bappu as the visitors raced off to a 7-0 start. The last man on the mat for Tamil Thalaivas, Manjeet Chhillar, went in to raid and picked up a bonus to get his team off the mark, but he too was tackled as the reigning champions inflicted an All-Out in just under seven minutes.

The home side fared much better after reassembling on the mat and outscored Bengaluru Bulls 5-2 over the next five minutes to cut their deficit to seven. Shabeer’s two-point raid and Thakur’s touch point on Nandal got the momentum on Tamil Thalaivas’ side. But three unanswered points from Bengaluru Bulls put them back up by eight points. Tamil Thalaivas added two more points to their score while allowing the visitors just one as the teams headed into the half-time break with Bengaluru Bulls leading 17-10.

After a cagey seven minutes in the second period, V Ajith Kumar’s touch point, followed by a Ran Singh tackle on Rohit Kumar, saw Tamil Thalaivas cut the deficit down to just four points. Thakur and Mohit Chhillar then added two more points to their team’s score to reduce Bengaluru Bulls down to just two.

But the Season 6 champions responded with a Super Tackle followed by a two-point raid by Ankit, which extended their lead back up to six. Nandal’s tackle on Ajith Kumar not only gave him his High 5 but also reduced Tamil Thalaivas down to three men on the mat. Two more raid points from Sehrawat and a self-out from Ran Singh helped Bengaluru Bulls inflict an All-Out and take an 11-point lead.

Both teams added a couple of points to their score over the final three minutes of the contest as Bengaluru Bulls emerged victors by 11 points.

Top Performers:

Bengaluru Bulls –

Best Raider – Pawan Sehrawat (11 Raid Points)

Best Defender – Saurabh Nandal (5 Tackle Points)

Tamil Thalaivas -  

Best Raider – Ajay Thakur (4 Raid Points)

Best Defender – Ran Singh (3 Tackle Points)

title: Pro Kabaddi 2019 Highlights | Dabang Delhi vs Patna Pirates | Hindi 66
description:
[Video Courtesy: Star Sports] Dabang Delhi K.C. see off Patna Pirates’ late surge to finish perfect at home

Trailing by 16 points, Patna Pirates managed to get within two in the closing stages but couldn’t get the victory over Dabang Delhi K.C.

A spirited comeback from Patna Pirates led by ‘Record-Breaker’ Pardeep Narwal fell agonizingly short as Dabang Delhi K.C. held their nerve in the dying moments to secure a 38-35 victory at the Thyagaraj Sports Complex in Delhi on Friday. With this win, the side from the capital extended their lead at the top of the vivo Pro Kabaddi Season 7 standings to 10 points. Raider Naveen Kumar scored, a record, ninth successive Super 10 to ensure that Dabang Delhi K.C. finish with a perfect record in their home leg.

Superstar raider Naveen and the defence got the home side off to a dream start, as the raider scored four raid points in his first three attempts and the defence added two tackle points which reduced Patna Pirates to a solitary man. Right Corner Ravinder Pahal made quick work of the raider and inflicted the game’s first All-Out on Patna Pirates to give his side a 10-3 lead.

Dabang Delhi K.C. rode their momentum and scored six more unanswered points which left Patna Pirates with just two men on the mat. Vikas Jaglan added three raid points to his team’s total but it wasn’t enough for Patna Pirates to avoid the All-Out, as Dabang Delhi K.C. took a 14-point lead.

The visitors fared much better over the final nine minutes of the first half. Skipper Pardeep, who was limited to just one raid point up until that point, scored a point each in successive raids before stunning the home side with a Super Raid that left them with a solitary man on the mat. Neeraj Kumar’s Thigh Hold then stopped the raider in his track and Patna Pirates inflicted the All-Out to cut the deficit to just eight. The home side then added a couple of points to their score, while Patna Pirates added one as the two teams went into the break with Dabang Delhi K.C. leading 26-17.

The gap between the two sides remained at eight seven minutes into the second half, however, Joginder Narwal’s tackle on Pardeep and a raid point each from Chandran Ranjit and Vijay extended that lead to 11. Some excellent work from Pardeep though brought the deficit back down to 10 and his two-point raid further cut into Dabang Delhi K.C.’s lead, while also reducing the hosts to two men. Patna Pirates defence’s seventh tackle point and Pardeep’s 15thraid point of match inflicted another All-Out on Dabang Delhi K.C. and cut their lead to just four.

Pardeep went on to add two more points to his team’s total which cut Patna Pirates’ deficit to just a couple of points, however, Naveen’s successful raid in a do-or-die situation gave his side a three-point lead with just over a minute left in the contest. Pardeep’s 18th raid point of the night gave his side a glimmer of hope but Joginder’s tackle on the Patna Pirates skipper in the buzzer raid confirmed Dabang Delhi K.C.’s narrow win.

Top Performers:

Dabang Delhi K.C.

Top Raider – Naveen Kumar (15 Raid Points)

Top Defender – Ravinder Pahal (4 Tackle Points)

Patna Pirates

Top Raider – Pardeep Narwal (18 Raid Points)

Top Defender – Vikas Jaglan (2 Tackle Points)

 In the 1960’s, the fate of earth was teetering on the brink of collapse. 2 superpowers, the United States of America and The Soviet Union, were deeply engaged in what we commonly call the Cold War.  It’s history’s biggest dick measuring contest.  A hellish arms race to complete annihilation.  If either side mustered the gall to pull the trigger, it would result in absolute destruction. title: 10 Unique Animals You Won’t Believe Exist
description:
10 strange and amazing animals that you have probably never heard of. Nature is truly full of surprises!
We live in the twenty-first century, and all continents have already been discovered, all secrets of our planet revealed, all mountain peaks conquered. Just when you think you have seen it all, some new bizarre creature makes an appearance instantly restoring your faith in the impossible! 

TIMESTAMPS
Mangalitsa Pig, a.k.a. “a pig in sheep’s clothing” 0:50
Rhinopithecus or golden snub-nosed monkey 1:33
Emperor tamarin 2:13
Patagonian Mara 3:04
Fluffy cow 3:52
Markhor Goat 4:44
Raccoon dog 5:23
Blue Footed Booby 6:25
Malayan Colugo 7:13
Venezuelan Poodle Moth 8:09
BONUS 8:56

SUMMARY
The birthplace of this curly-haired pig is Hungary where it was discovered in the mid-19th century. Due to the fleece covering this animal, it resembles a sheep, therefore, such a name! 
The name of this species is roxellana, and there is a story behind it. It is believed that they were called this way after the supposedly snub-nosed courtesan of Suleiman the Magnificent (a 16th century Sultan of the Ottoman Empire). 
They were called like this because of the resemblance of their mustache to that of German Emperor Wilhelm II. 
Patagonia Mara is the fourth largest rodent on our planet. There are several interesting facts about them. Females often put offsprings into crèches for safety. 
Fluffy cows are looked after by people whose work is to wash, dry and use products to style these animals, so they look as fluffy as they do! It is necessary to maintain them daily, and it will take months of regular grooming until they get this lovely look of kids toys.
If you see a creature which looks as if it’s trying to catch an alien radio signal from space, it’s most likely Markhor Goat. They can grow as long as 6 ft from head to tail! 
If you can’t decide if you want to have a dog or a raccoon as a pet, we have just the thing for you - raccoon dog! Despite having raccoon-like markings on their fur, they are not very closely related to the North American raccoon. 
Blue Footed Booby are to catch your eye if you ever visit the Galapagos Islands. They can look a bit clumsy and comical on land, but they are excellent at flying and swimming. 
Colugo has a large gliding membrane (like a flying squirrel), and they can glide for long distances between trees standing far apart. 
Even if the Poodle Moth may look as if it lives in Antarctica with all this fur, in fact, it comes from Venezuela, a tropical country. Its hairs don’t serve for heating. 

BONUS
Cloud Antelope! This species lives in the clouds (that’s why such a name)! Its bright blue fur is the reflection of cloudless blue skies in the area of its habitat. Its diet consists of sun rays and candies...
